author: @esepecesito
text: For the metric folks:¬† 100g Flour for each egg.¬†(1 egg + 100g flour is conveniently one "normal" pasta portion) Salt 8g per litre of water. The time in the fridge is not strictly necessary. I never do it. I use the the thicker setting to avoid work, after a little bit of mixing the eggs and the flour, I pass it several times through the machine to achieve a nice texture. Then proceed as explained, each time finer. Cooking time depends strongly on thickness of pasta: from 3-4 minutes for real thing, to 10 min for thick pasta.
